
Git & GitHub for DevOps Workshop
====================================

1) What is Git ?

Git is a Distributed Version Control System (DVCS) used to track, manage, and maintain source code. It allows developers to:

- Maintain complete version history of projects

- Share code securely with team members

- Work simultaneously without conflicts

- Create branches for new features and bug fixes

- Merge changes efficiently

- Roll back to previous versions when needed






2) What is GitHub, GitLab & Bitbucket ?

GitHub, GitLab, and Bitbucket are Source Code Management (SCM) platforms that use Git as their underlying version control technology. They provide powerful features that help teams:

- Create and manage repositories

- Track and control code versions

- Collaborate with team members efficiently

- Review code using pull/merge requests

- Maintain code history and audit trails

- Integrate CI/CD pipelines for automation

- Manage access control and permissions




