git reset --hard 'commit_id'

git logs





================================

When the File or Code is in File-System it is in "Un-Tracked" Status

When we do "git add <file_name>" the Code is in "Staged" Status

When we do "git commit -m 'commit_message'" the Code is in "Tracked" Status






================================

If we want to Push the Code from Git to GitHub we will follow below mentioned steps:

- git remote add origin "github_url" 

- git branch -M main

- git push -u origin main


# If we want to change the url of the Origin then we can use the below Command

- git remote set-url "https://PAT@github.com/REPO_NAME"






================================

We can Either Fork the GitHub Repository  [Fork Happens GitHub To GitHub]

OR

We Can Clone the GitHub Repository  [Clone Happens GitHub To Local]






























